  "prompt": "How is demonetization affecting people of India?",
  "response": "Demonetization in India, implemented in November 2016 by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, had several significant impacts:\n\nPositive Effects:\n1. Reduced cash circulation in the black economy\n2. Increased digital transaction adoption\n3. Improved tax compliance\n4. Reduced counterfeit currency\n5. Increased bank account penetration\n\nNegative Effects:\n1. Short-term economic slowdown\n2. Significant cash crunch\n3. Job losses, especially in informal sectors\n4. Disruption of small businesses\n5. Agricultural sector severely impacted\n6. People faced hardships exchanging old currency notes\n7. Long queues at banks and ATMs\n8. Reduced consumer spending\n9. Temporary economic downturn\n\nLong-term Consequences:\n1. Increased digital financial infrastructure\n2. Greater financial transparency\n3. Formalization of the economy\n4. Enhanced digital payment systems\n\nOverall, demonetization had mixed results, with short-term challenges but potential long-term economic benefits. Economists and experts continue to debate its overall effectiveness and impact on the Indian economy.",
